More than a thousand twitchers travelled to Somerset after a rare bird was spotted for only the third time in the UK .
They descended on the West Country when a Hudsonian Godwit made a 4,000 mile detour from South America .
It is believed the large shorebird - heading to its breeding grounds in Canada and Alaska - was last seen in 1988 .
More than 1,000 bird watchers and photographers lined the water 's edge to catch a glimpse of the bird .